verses.text_plain: Hear my prayer, O Lord, give ear to my supplications: in thy faithfulness answer me, and in thy righteousness.
verses.verse_html: 1Hear my prayer, O Lord, give ear to my supplications: in thy faithfulness answer me, and in thy righteousness.

verses.text_plain: And enter not into judgment with thy servant: for in thy sight shall no man living be justified.
verses.verse_html: 2And enter not into judgment with thy servant: for in thy sight shall no man living be justified.

verses.text_plain: For the enemy hath persecuted my soul; he hath smitten my life down to the ground; he hath made me to dwell in darkness, as those that have been long dead.
verses.verse_html: 3For the enemy hath persecuted my soul; he hath smitten my life down to the ground; he hath made me to dwell in darkness, as those that have been long dead.

tokens.text: he hath made me to dwell
as those that have been long

verses.text_plain: Therefore is my spirit overwhelmed within me; my heart within me is desolate.
verses.verse_html: 4Therefore is my spirit overwhelmed within me; my heart within me is desolate.

verses.text_plain: I remember the days of old; I meditate on all thy works; I muse on the work of thy hands.
verses.verse_html: 5I remember the days of old; I meditate on all thy works; I muse on the work of thy hands.

verses.text_plain: I stretch forth my hands unto thee: my soul thirsteth after thee, as a thirsty land. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 6I stretch forth my hands unto thee: my soul thirsteth after thee, as a thirsty land. Selah.

verses.text_plain: Hear me speedily, O Lord: my spirit faileth: hide not thy face from me, lest I be like unto them that go down into the pit.
verses.verse_html:
7Hear me speedily, O Lord: my spirit faileth: hide not thy face from me, lest I be like unto them that go down into the pit. ▼
▼ lest…: or, for I am become like, etc

tokens.text: from me, lest I be like

footnotes.body_text: ▼ lest…: or, for I am become like, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ lest…: or, for I am become like, etc

verses.text_plain: Cause me to hear thy lovingkindness in the morning; for in thee do I trust: cause me to know the way wherein I should walk; for I lift up my soul unto thee.
verses.verse_html: 8Cause me to hear thy lovingkindness in the morning; for in thee do I trust: cause me to know the way wherein I should walk; for I lift up my soul unto thee.

tokens.text: for in thee do I trust

verses.text_plain: Deliver me, O Lord, from mine enemies: I flee unto thee to hide me.
verses.verse_html:
9Deliver me, O Lord, from mine enemies: I flee unto thee to hide me. ▼
▼ flee…: Heb. hide me with thee

tokens.text: I flee unto thee to hide

footnotes.body_text: ▼ flee…: Heb. hide me with thee
footnotes.body_html: ▼ flee…: Heb. hide me with thee

verses.text_plain: Teach me to do thy will; for thou art my God: thy spirit is good; lead me into the land of uprightness.
verses.verse_html: 10Teach me to do thy will; for thou art my God: thy spirit is good; lead me into the land of uprightness.

verses.text_plain: Quicken me, O Lord, for thy name’s sake: for thy righteousness’ sake bring my soul out of trouble.
verses.verse_html: 11Quicken me, O Lord, for thy name’s sake: for thy righteousness’ sake bring my soul out of trouble.

verses.text_plain: And of thy mercy cut off mine enemies, and destroy all them that afflict my soul: for I am thy servant.
verses.verse_html: 12And of thy mercy cut off mine enemies, and destroy all them that afflict my soul: for I am thy servant.
